    "86039330": {
      "title": "A persistent virus infection in Feldmannia (Phaeophyceae)",
      "abstract": "A virus infection is described within the unilocular sporangia of Feldmannia spn., a filamentous brown alga (Phaeophyceae). The alga is easily maintained in culture and vegetative growth is vigorous, but formation of icosahedral virions 150 nm in diameter completely displaces production of zoospores. The viruses, estimated at 1-5 × 10 6 per sporangium, are eventually released by rupture of the sporangial wall. Deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) isolated from the viruses can be readily digested with restriction endonucleases and consists of ca. 170 kbp of double-stranded DNA (...)"
